article.headline: Akron 73, Radford 63
article.story: RADFORD, Va. (AP) -- Jeremiah Wood scored 24 points and grabbed 13 rebounds to lead Akron to a 73-63 second-half comeback win over Radford on Saturday. Akron, (1-1), mounted a second-half 9-0 run and then a 15-0 run with 8:09 left in the game to overcome what had a 30-23 Radford lead at the half. Wood hit 10 of 13 from the field and was helped by Derrick Tarver, who scored 17 points and made 8 of 9 from the free-throw line. Radford, (3-1), jumped to a 20-9 lead with 6:10 left in the first half. The Highlanders were led by Whit Holcomb-Faye and Chris Goodin, who each had 17 points.
